From its inception, The Club at Admirals Cove was envisioned as a community like no other. Enviably located on the Intracoastal Waterway, member-owned, and possessing an immense wealth of amenities, this is a truly exceptional community where family life flourishes. Members make lifelong friendships, become golfing and fishing buddies, tennis partners, and more. The club is as careful to cultivate and preserve this close-knit camaraderie as its stunning natural setting and traditional member events. That commitment to excellence is well recognized with Distinguished Club, Platinum Clubs of America, and Platinum Clubs of the World honors. Most recently, Admirals Cove’s General Manager, Brett Morris, was named 2022 Club Executive of the Year by Club Management magazine. This sun-soaked, secluded oasis is home to families and friends who share a love of nature, active living, and the finer things in life. The modern, comprehensive amenities they enjoy are impressive: 45 holes of golf, tennis and pickleball, a private marina, an array of dining options, modern wellness facilities, a private boutique hotel, and more, all inside the community’s gates. This is one of the few clubs in Jupiter with its own marina (offering dockage for vessels as large as 165 feet). Back on shore, the incredible Bluewater Wellness Spa & Salon elevates pampering to a true art form. The golf, routed along scenic waterways, is magnificent. Admirals Cove is recognized as one of Florida’s best private golf clubs, and its challenging 45 holes bear witness to that. They’ve been honored to host the U.S. Open Qualifier for over a decade. In early 2023, members will enjoy a new 4,800-square-foot, state-of-the-art Golf Performance Center with the most technologically advanced teaching equipment and software in the industry. There is a unique sense of pride among those fortunate to call Admirals Cove home. Its residents’ generous and caring nature is evident in their participation in the Admirals Cove Foundation, which focuses on charitable education, health, and human services. Those looking to call Admirals Cove home can contact Membership Director Kelly Icsman at kicsman@admiralscove.net .
